ASSIGNMENT #1 (Group):  Communication Covenant due January 11
	 
	A Communication Covenant is an agreement every member of a team makes about communicating: 
	·  	promising to communicate regularly (even when the news is bad),
	·  	promising to answer your email how many times a day,
	·  	agreeing that you will be using Google Docs for file management,
	·  	specifying when and where your meetings are (1-2 times a week),
	·  	promising to notify team mates if you can’t make a meeting,
	·  	agreeing to reasonable punishments if a team mate is late or misses without notifying everyone,
	·  	promising to volunteer to do things and to do them well and on time. 
	 
	Include a table of preferred email addresses and cell phone numbers.  Title the file TEAMNAMEContacts
	 
	Put this file in the Google Docs folder your team is sharing with us.

Communication Covenant
Overview
The purpose of this communication covenant is to establish team roles, maintain a way to keep track of meeting schedules and deadlines, determine the most effective means of communication among team members, determine a set time and place for meetings, and define team member code of conduct.
 
Team Roles
For every meeting, there will be one team member who will take on the role of meeting facilitator. This role will be rotated every two weeks. This person will be responsible for scheduling, coordinating, setting up an end time for the meeting, and ensuring that the all topics are covered before the end time. This person is also responsible for ensuring that tasks be completed before the deadline.
All members will be active during the meeting and will ensure that they are well prepared.
 
Team Meetings
We will be meeting every Monday and Wednesday at 5:30 PM at the Science Library. Every meeting will have an end time that will be determined by the meeting facilitator. All members are required to attend and arrive on time. If a member cannot attend, they should inform the rest of the team members as soon as possible. If a member is late or misses a meeting without notifying another team member, they will have to provide pizza for all members in the next meeting.
 
Calendar
We will be maintaining a calendar on Google Calendar with all our meeting dates and deadlines. If any changes are made by a member, an email should be sent out to the rest of the team informing them of this change.
 
Communication Methods
Email will be our primary method of communication. Email should be checked twice a day, once in the morning and once in the evening. Emails should be responded to promptly and responses should be expected within 4 hours. Even if a member does not have all the work done in response to the email, the member will respond to acknowledge that they have seen the email.
 
Texting and calling may be used for a more urgent response.
 
File Management
We will be using GoogleDocs for file management and information sharing.
       
Team Member Code of Conduct
All team members will take an active role in the project and contribute equally.
Members shall treat each other with respect. If any member feels as if the work is not contributed equally or feels that another member is not doing enough to contribute, the issue will be brought up during a meeting. If a team member fails to contribute or consecutively misses meetings, the issue will be brought to the instructor.
